acing. First-principles calculations\nreveal that the strong noncovalent cation-pi interactions between hydrated\ncations in solution and aromatic ring structures in GO are the cause of this\nunexpected behavior. These findings open up new avenues for using GO membranes\nfor water desalination and purification, lithium-based batteries and\nsuper-capacitors, molecular sieves for separating ions or molecules, and many\nother applications.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 20 Oct 2016 11:43:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-10-21"}
